This paper is about interactive image segmentation, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new approach based on quadratic optimization problems related to dominant sets, which is a graph-theoretic notion (cs.GR). The approach involves controlling a regularization parameter, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions dealing with different input modalities, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM). Overall, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, and cs.MM.
